body:
I think it does not worth adding a new test for this.

Also note that although `store.put` may still throw a `KafkaException` or `StreamException`, since it is not documented in javadocs users should not expect to capture them at all in their own code, especially `try-catch` all exceptions like:

```
try {
    store.put(key, value);
catch (Exception e) {   // or even catch (Throwable t)
    // handle them..
}
```

cc @xvrl

This PR is blocked by https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/KAFKA-5603 now. 

DO NOT MERGE

@xiaotao183 Thanks for your comment. I understand your concern. Maybe, quotas need to be revised for this case to allow a more flexible quota assignment to multiple clients as a group (but I am not familiar with the details.) @guozhangwang @ijuma Can you comment on this?
